<section xml:id="sec-eigenvalues-eigenvectors-sagemath">
	<title>Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors using SageMath</title>
	<introduction>The computer algebra system SageMath can compute eigenvalues and eigenvectors of a given matrix. Please do the relevant changes on this page to verify your calculations.</introduction>
	<p>
		In the following examples QQ denotes the field of rational numbers. You may change it to RR, the field of real numbers. Numbers in brackets are rows of <m>A</m>. You can change number of rows as well as entries of rows.
	</p>
	<p>
		<alert>Computation of eigenvalues</alert>
		<sage>
		<input>
			sage: A=matrix(QQ,[[1,0,1],[1,0,1],[2,-2,2]]); A
			sage: A.eigenvalues()
		</input>
	</sage>
	</p>

	<p>
		<alert>Computation of eigenvectors</alert>
				<sage>
		<input>
			sage: A=matrix(QQ,[[1,0,1],[1,0,1],[2,-2,2]]); A
			sage: A.eigenvectors_right()
	</input>
	</sage>
	</p>

	<p>
		<alert>Computation of eigenspaces</alert>
		<sage>
			<input>
				sage: A=matrix(QQ,[[1,0,1],[1,0,1],[2,-2,2]]); A
				sage: A.eigenspaces_right()
			</input>
		</sage>
	</p>
</section>